‚óŹ The build fails before producing verbose output. The pkg_config crate with
  .statik(true) emits cargo:rustc-link-lib=static= directives automatically
  during .probe(). The .pc files might contain : prefixed lib references that
  the crate can't handle.

  Let me check the .pc files:

  Read 1 file (ctrl+o to expand)

‚óŹ The -l:librte_bus_pci.a syntax (colon prefix) is the problem. The pkg_config
  crate doesn't handle this syntax properly ‚ÄĒ it strips the -l but leaves
  :librte_bus_pci.a or just an empty string.

  The better approach is to avoid using pkg_config for DPDK linking and instead
  manually link the static DPDK libraries. Let me switch to a more direct
  approach.

  Listed 2 directories (ctrl+o to expand)

‚óŹ The approach of using pkg_config with .statik(true) is problematic because it
  automatically emits cargo:rustc-link-lib directives. The DPDK .pc files use
  -l:libfoo.a syntax which the Rust pkg-config crate can't handle.

  I need to rewrite the build script to not use pkg_config for automatic link
  emission. Instead, I'll use it only for discovering include paths and manually
   specify the libraries.

